  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) adapts large pre-trained models by updating "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "a small subset of parameters",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " — typically low-rank adapter matrices — while keeping base weights frozen. For agent builders, PEFT makes it practical to specialize models on tool formats, domain tone, or company workflows on consumer GPUs or managed fine-tuning APIs without full-weight copies per tenant."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "PEFT methods insert trainable modules into a frozen backbone. LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) adds low-rank decomposition matrices to attention projections; adapters are small bottleneck layers; prefix and prompt tuning prepend learnable virtual tokens. After training, adapter weights merge into the base model or ship as small sidecar files swapped at load time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full fine-tuning updates every parameter — expensive in GPU memory and storage when serving many specialized agents. PEFT trains 0.1%–2% of parameters yet often matches full FT on narrow tasks. Multi-tenant agent platforms store one base model plus per-customer LoRA adapters instead of duplicating 7B–70B checkpoints."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Benefits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lower VRAM",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — train adapters on single GPUs that cannot hold full FT optimizer states"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Small artifacts",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — LoRA checkpoints are megabytes, not gigabytes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Composable",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — swap adapters per tenant or task without reloading the base model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Less catastrophic forgetting",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — frozen backbone preserves general capabilities"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Faster iteration",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — shorter training runs for behavioral tweaks on agent trajectories"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Peak quality on broad tasks may trail full fine-tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hyperparameters (rank, target modules, learning rate) require tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Not all layers equally benefit from adapters — wrong target modules waste capacity"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Merged adapters are static; many concurrent LoRAs at inference need framework support"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Alignment-sensitive agent behavior may still need RLHF/DPO stages beyond supervised LoRA"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LoRA"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a frozen weight matrix W, LoRA learns ΔW = B·A where B ∈ ℝ^{d×r}, A ∈ ℝ^{r×k}, rank r ≪ min(d,k). Forward pass uses W + ΔW. Only A and B receive gradients. Rank controls capacity — r=8–64 is common for 7B agent fine-tunes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Other PEFT methods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Adapters",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — bottleneck FFN modules inserted between transformer layers"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefix / prompt tuning",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — learnable prefix vectors prepended to keys and values"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "IA³",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — learned scalers on activations"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "QLoRA",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — quantize base model to 4-bit; train LoRA in higher precision (detailed in LoRA/QLoRA subtopic)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Specializing an instruct model on consistent tool-call JSON or internal API shapes"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Per-tenant tone, compliance phrasing, or domain vocabulary on a shared base model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "GPU or budget constraints rule out full fine-tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Rapid A/B of behavioral variants by swapping small adapter files"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When not to use it"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fundamental capability gaps — PEFT nudges behavior; it does not teach entirely new skills from tiny data"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "When full weight updates and maximum quality on broad distributions justify the cost"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompting plus RAG already solves the task with less operational overhead"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How to implement"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fine-tune an agent-style dataset with Hugging Face PEFT and LoRA:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from datasets import Dataset\nfrom transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer, TrainingArguments, Trainer\nfrom peft import LoraConfig, get_peft_model, TaskType\n\nmodel_id = \"meta-llama/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct\"\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_id)\ntokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n\nbase = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n    model_id, torch_dtype=\"auto\", device_map=\"auto\"\n)\n\nlora_config = LoraConfig(\n    task_type=TaskType.CAUSAL_LM,\n    r=16,\n    lora_alpha=32,\n    lora_dropout=0.05,\n    target_modules=[\"q_proj\", \"v_proj\"],\n    bias=\"none\",\n)\nmodel = get_peft_model(base, lora_config)\nmodel.print_trainable_parameters()  # ~0.1% trainable\n\nexamples = [\n    {\"text\": \"<|user|>\\nRefund order 8812\\n<|assistant|>\\n\"\n             '{\"tool\": \"refund_order\", \"order_id\": \"8812\"}'},\n]\nds = Dataset.from_list(examples)\n\ndef tokenize(batch):\n    return tokenizer(batch[\"text\"], truncation=True, max_length=512)\n\ntokenized = ds.map(tokenize, batched=True)\n\nargs = TrainingArguments(\n    output_dir=\"./agent-lora\",\n    per_device_train_batch_size=1,\n    num_train_epochs=3,\n    learning_rate=2e-4,\n    logging_steps=1,\n    save_strategy=\"epoch\",\n)\ntrainer = Trainer(model=model, args=args, train_dataset=tokenized)\ntrainer.train()\nmodel.save_pretrained(\"./agent-lora-adapter\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Load a trained adapter at inference without copying the full base weights:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from peft import PeftModel\nfrom transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM\n\nmodel_id = \"meta-llama/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct\"\nbase = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(model_id, device_map=\"auto\")\nmodel = PeftModel.from_pretrained(base, \"./agent-lora-adapter\")\nmodel.eval()\n# Generate with adapted tool-format behavior"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Examples"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A 7B base model (~14 GB fp16) plus a rank-16 LoRA adapter (~50 MB) teaches stable refund-tool JSON. Three enterprise tenants load the same base with three adapter files — memory overhead is three small delta tensors, not three full models."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A SaaS agent platform hosts Llama-3-8B-Instruct once on each GPU worker. Customers upload conversation logs; the platform trains overnight LoRA adapters for tool-use formatting. At request time, routing metadata selects the tenant adapter via PEFT dynamic loading. Full-model fine-tuning was rejected after cost projections showed 40× storage and deployment complexity versus adapter swapping."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Training on poorly formatted chat data without applying the model's chat template"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Setting rank too low for complex format changes or too high without regularization"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Targeting only one projection matrix when task needs broader representation shift"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluating on training prompts only — adapters overfit small agent trajectory sets quickly"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Confusing PEFT with full fine-tuning alignment — supervised LoRA does not replace DPO/RLHF for preference tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Curate diverse agent trajectories including edge cases and refusals"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Match chat template and special tokens to production inference"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Start with r=8–16 on q_proj and v_proj; expand target_modules if underfitting"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Hold out scenario-based eval sets mirroring live agent tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Version adapter files alongside base model revision and tokenizer"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Performance and scalability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Training time and memory scale with adapter parameters, not full model size — QLoRA pushes this further by quantizing the frozen base. Inference with unmerged adapters adds small matmul overhead; merging eliminates runtime cost. For many concurrent tenant adapters, use serving frameworks with multi-LoRA batching or pre-merge hot adapters."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tooling and ecosystem"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "peft (Hugging Face)",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — LoRA, adapters, prompt tuning, load/save adapters"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "trl",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — SFTTrainer integrates PEFT for supervised fine-tuning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "bitsandbytes",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — 4/8-bit quantization for QLoRA training"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Unsloth / Axolotl",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — optimized LoRA training recipes for open models"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Managed APIs",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — OpenAI, Together, and others offer LoRA-style fine-tuning endpoints"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Comparison with alternatives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Full fine-tuning",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — updates all weights; highest flexibility and cost; see fine-tuning sibling topic"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompting + RAG",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — no weight updates; fastest iteration; less consistent on format-heavy agent tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Distillation",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — train smaller model from teacher outputs; complementary to PEFT specialization"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
